                  <t:desc type="foundation">According to the local tradition, the founder was "šǝm Bagunāy" (a governor of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2002Bugna">Bugnā</t:placeName>?); in the time of King <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4015Fasilada">Fāsiladas</t:persName> (r. <t:date notBefore="1632" notAfter="1667">1632-1667</t:date>). 
                     But according to Additio 5 of BMQM-006, the church was founded during the 6th year of the reign of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5636IyoasI">King ʾIyoʾās</t:persName> (=<t:date when="1761">1761 A.D.</t:date>)</t:desc>
